parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inoperative Automatic Shoulder and Lap Belts
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of automatic shoulder and lap belts can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident, as occupants may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: The driver's side and passenger's side automatic shoulder and lap belts are inoperable
the belts do not retract
the belts do not lock
the belts are stuck
the belts are broken.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Seat Belt Plastic Clip Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the plastic clip on the rear seat belts can cause the belts to become inoperable, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The plastic clip on the rear seat belts has disintegrated
the rear seat belts are inoperable
the rear seat belts are stuck
the rear seat belts are broken.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Delayed or Unavailable Seat Belt Repair Parts
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay or unavailability of seat belt repair parts can lead to prolonged periods of inoperable seat belts, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Difficulty obtaining seat belt recall parts
delayed seat belt repair
unavailable seat belt repair parts.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Seat Belt Housing Bracket or Buckle Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt housing bracket or buckle can cause the seat belts to become inoperable, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt housing bracket broke
the seat belt buckle brackets/locking mechanism fell apart
the seat belt buckle is stuck
the seat belt buckle is broken.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden stalling of the engine can cause loss of control, accidents, or leave the driver stranded, especially when it occurs at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The engine dies or cuts off while driving
the vehicle stalls out without warning
the computer fails
the vehicle loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning horn can increase the risk of accidents, as the driver is unable to alert other road users of their presence or intentions.
symptoms: The horn is inoperative
the horn does not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration Due to Electronic Throttle Control Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, posing a significant risk to the driver, passengers, and other road users.
symptoms: The vehicle surges forward at a high rate of speed
especially when engaging the automatic transmission into reverse
the throttle sticks in a position
the cruise control comes on by itself even when turned off
and sudden acceleration occurs without driver input.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Locking Issue in Wet Conditions
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brakes locking up in wet conditions can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Brakes lock up when driving in wet conditions
even after new brake pads and master cylinder have been installed
requiring continuous pumping to release
and repeating the issue after the brakes dry out.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Premature Brake Wear and Increased Stopping Distance
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake wear can lead to reduced stopping power, increased stopping distance, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Brake pads wear out prematurely
requiring frequent replacements
and the brake pedal requires excessive foot pressure to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion-related brake failure can cause loss of braking power, leading to accidents and potentially injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Rear brake pads corrode
requiring replacement
and potentially causing brake failure.
